begin_memory_text: We talked about our schedules, what we had been up to today. I discussed the difference in my work pre-COVID and during COVID.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our partners, how to cook certain meals, availability of Asian markets in our neighborhood.
end_memory_text: We talked about how we have been feeling during quarantine. We shared how it was weird to have all this free time and feeling guilty that you aren't being productive and taking a break.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week will be the same, just work until Thursday. I have pretty slow days at work now so it is relaxing. Also, I will be able to see my sister today for dinner so that will be a plus. I will try to be productive for the rest of the week.
critical_positive: We both asked questions about each others' lives and took turns answering questions. It worked well because we had similarities between us where we could relate to one another, so we could talk a lot together about one topic. Also, she kept up the conversation and did not make it feel one-sided.
critical_negative: I always feel uncomfortable when a conversation goes silent, but I should know that that is normal in a conversation. But I felt somewhat pressured to carry the conversation and switch topics once I felt we talked enough about one topic. I also get nervous a bit when I first meet someone.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, and we talked about where each of us lives. We also talked about how we're doing in the current pandemic. The other person talked about their work and living with their partner; I talked about living with my partner. We talked about healthcare, and where my partner goes to school. We talked about the kinds of people who become doctors.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about food! Cooking, etc. I talked about the food that I cook at home, and the other person talked about the food that they eat at home. I talked a little about the curry that I made. We talked about how their partner doesn't like vegetables. Talked about grocery shopping.
end_memory_text: Talked about how they're going to have hotpot with their sister and their partner! I asked for tips about how to make hotpot. We talked about Asian stores, I asked what they tend to buy. Talked about eating during COVID. Talked about talking with friends and family, and also talked about low energy. Mentioned that it was a good chat. Then finished.
rest_of_day_open: I think that it will go OK. It won't be perfect, but I hope that it will work out. Realistically, I probably won't get as much done as I would like... And I will probably get very stressed some nights. I'll also have to spend a good bit of energy with cooking. Ok, now I'm a little sad.
critical_positive: I think that both people tried to keep the conversation going. We both asked questions of the other, and it felt like the conversation developed organically. Neither person pried too much. Additionally, we found some small things in common--age, food, etc. I also think that we both had similar, upbeat energy, and that kind of fed into itself and kept the conversation interesting (and not boring).
critical_negative: I sometimes would speak while they were speaking, which ended up interrupting them. I noticed that they would stop talking if I were to speak, even if it interrupted their train of thought. Additionally, there were a few pauses where we both were trying to think of where to go next. And, while the conversation WAS upbeat and energetic, it was also a bit tiring once the emotions started to wear off.
